    "CONTROL FLOW STATEMENTS"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "4928acfc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "'''..>CONTROL FLOW stmts are the instructions that determine the order in which your code is executed\n",
    "..>By default, python runs code line by line from top to bottom(Sequential),\n",
    "..>but control flow statments allow you to skip sections, repeat tasks or choose between diff paths\n",
    "\n",
    "..> These are categorized in to three types \n",
    "(Default..sequentional control flow..this is default mode,python reads your code like a book from top to bottom,one line\n",
    "at a time..unless you tell it otherwise,every line executes in the order it was written)\n",
    ">>>>conditional/selection/decision making stmts\n",
    ">>>>iteration/repetition(Loops)\n",
    ">>>>jump/transfer stmts'''"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
